name: Teviot Row House, Edinburgh, Edinburgh EH8 9AJ, UK
directions: Top floor of main stairwell, clearly signposted.

name: Caffè Nero
directions: Towards the back of the cafe, on the right.
comment: You have to be a "paying customer." As well as the unisex/gender neutral toilet, there are also gendered single stall toilets in this cafe.

name: Caffe Nero
comment: 2 locking single stalls, not gendered. It is very easy to get to the loos without passing by any staff. Just go in the door, up the steps, and turn right and follow the sign. Because it's a coffee shop, it's nice if you buy something but not necessary.

name: Salt Horse Beer Shop and Bar
National Library of Scotland
directions: On the ground floor, through the visitor area and on the right
comment: Four gender neutral individual toilets. NLS is free to enter, so no need to buy anything etc

name: YO! Sushi
directions: All toilets single person rooms.
comment: You have to buy food.

name: National Library of Scotland
comment: Free :)

name: Augustine United Church
comment: Former Church Member

name: New York Steam Packet
directions: By the entrance, ground floor,can sneak in without witnesses.
comment: Great BYOB grillhouse, lovely staff, anarchist cafe-cum-restarant with good value wo and three course meals from noon until late.

name: Harmonium
directions: Downstairs in basement with one way system.
comment: Doors say "cubicles only" and "cubicles and urinals", rather than designated by gender.

name: Coro the Chocolate Cafe
directions: On the left as you go in
comment: Most likely have to be a paying customer

name: TexMex 2
directions: 2 single toilets, although they are gendered and quite small.
comment: Since it's a restaurant, you will have to buy something, but you could probably get away with a margarita or a Mexican beer if you don't want food.

name: Teviot Row House
directions: On the second floor, next to the Dining Room

name: Henderson's Hollyrood
comment: *think you would have to be a paying customer

name: Lister Learning and Teaching Centre
directions: Ground floor and through a door to the right. Single accessible washroom. Several single-user non-gendered washrooms.

name: Hemma
directions: Gender neutral upstairs.

name: The Forest
directions: Accessible toilet is in the main cafe, other genderfree toilets downstairs in the basement.
comment: Forest is a wacky awesome place, run by volunteers and spontaneously exploding with creativity here and there. Don't be surprised if these aren't the cleanest toilets ever though!

name: Teviot Row House
directions: Go up the main stair to the second floor and then through the door on the left
comment: This is a student union building but you don't have to be a student to go in.

name: University of Edinburgh Old Medical School, William Robertson Wing
LGBT health and well-being
comment: Only if you are a LGBT community service members only open when events are on at the centre

name: LGBT Centre for Health and Wellbeing
directions: Ring buzzer and someone will let you in.
comment: This is the LGBT Centre's location so they will definitely be a safe place. Likely to only be open certain hours, but worth a try if you need somewhere that's definitely safe.
